'''James Lee Williams''' (12 April 1992 – 5 January 2025), known professionally as '''The Vivienne''', was a British [[drag performer]], known for being appointed as the UK drag ambassador in 2015 for American reality television series ''[[RuPaul's Drag Race]]''. They later competed in and won the [[RuPaul's Drag Race UK series 1|first series]] of ''[[RuPaul's Drag Race UK]]'' in 2019, and competed again in the [[RuPaul's Drag Race All Stars season 7|seventh season]] of ''[[RuPaul's Drag Race All Stars]]'' in 2022. They became the first drag performer to compete on ''[[Dancing on Ice]]'' in 2023, appearing as a contestant on the [[Dancing on Ice series 15|fifteenth series]], in which they finished in third place.

The Vivienne delved into other ventures such as releasing their debut [[extended play]] (EP), ''Bitch on Heels'' (2022). They starred as the [[Wicked Witch of the West]] for [[The Wizard of Oz (2011 musical)|''The Wizard of Oz'']] in the 2024 UK tour.

== Early life and education ==
Williams was born and raised in [[North Wales]] and moved to Liverpool at 16 years old. They attended [[Rydal Penrhos]] in Colwyn Bay; Wales.<ref>{{cite web |last=Nanji |first=Noor |title=RuPaul's Drag Race UK star The Vivienne dies aged 32 |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c4gw1v51yezo |access-date=5 January 2025 |website=bbc.com |publisher=[[British Broadcasting Corporation]] |archive-date=5 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250105200319/https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c4gw1v51yezo |url-status=live}}</ref> They were of [[Romani people|Romani]] heritage.<ref>{{Cite web |date=19 November 2019 |title=The Vivienne on Her Early Days of Drag: 'They Offered Me a Blue WKD and 30 Quid' |url=https://graziadaily.co.uk/life/tv-and-film/rupaul-drag-race-vivienne/ |access-date=10 March 2022 |archive-date=10 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220310085729/https://graziadaily.co.uk/life/tv-and-film/rupaul-drag-race-vivienne/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

== Career ==
Williams was given the name The Vivienne, because they were known for wearing [[Vivienne Westwood]] clothing, adding the definite article to make it unique. Their first [[drag show]] was located in [[Liverpool]] and they worked in various bars such as Superstar Boudoir.<ref>{{cite web |title=No ordinary label queen: The Vivienne |url=https://vadamagazine.com/entertainment/arts/the-vivienne-an-interview |date=19 September 2015 |access-date=3 December 2024 |website=Vada Magazine }}</ref> The Vivienne competed in a one-day event judged by [[RuPaul]], [[Katie Price]], and [[Jonathan Ross]], taking place at [[Café de Paris, London|Café de Paris]], where they were placed in the top two alongside drag performer [[La Voix (drag queen)|La Voix]], and then crowned as the UK Ambassador for ''[[RuPaul's Drag Race]]'' on 28 May 2015.<ref>{{cite magazine |last=Bond |first=Nick |title=RuPaul crowns her UK ''Drag Race'' ambassador |url=https://www.attitude.co.uk/culture/film-tv/rupaul-crowns-her-uk-drag-race-ambassador-284820/ |date=7 September 2017 |access-date=3 December 2024 |magazine=[[Attitude (magazine)|Attitude]] |archive-date=4 December 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241204015715/https://www.attitude.co.uk/culture/film-tv/rupaul-crowns-her-uk-drag-race-ambassador-284820/ |url-status=live }}</ref> The Vivienne was later flown to Los Angeles and made a [[New Wave Queens|cameo appearance]] for the [[RuPaul's Drag Race season 8|eighth season]] of ''RuPaul's Drag Race'' (2016).<ref>{{cite magazine |last=Dey |first=David |title=RuPaul crowns first ever UK Drag Ambassador: The Vivienne |url=https://www.out.com/popnography/2015/5/29/rupaul-crowns-first-ever-uk-drag-ambassador-vivienne |date=29 May 2015 |access-date=3 December 2024 |magazine=[[Out (magazine)|Out]] |archive-date=3 December 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241203133554/https

