'''Tim Bergling'''{{efn|{{IPA|sv|ˈtɪmː ˈbæ̂rjlɪŋ|-|sv-Tim Bergling.ogg|small=no}}.}} (8 September 1989 – 20 April 2018), known professionally as '''Avicii''',{{efn|Pronounced {{IPAc-en|ə|ˈ|v|iː|tʃ|i}} {{respell|ə|VEE|chee}} in English, {{IPA|sv|aˈvɪ̌tːɕɪ|}} in Swedish.}}<!-- Please do not add stylisations --> was a Swedish [[DJ]], remixer, and [[record producer]]. At age 16, he began posting his [[remix]]es on electronic music forums, which led to his first record deal.<ref name=" Avicii obituary">{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2018/apr/22/avicii-obituary |title=Avicii obituary |last=McIver |first=Joel |date=22 April 2018 |work=The Guardian |access-date=22 April 2018 |archive-date=21 June 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180621171028/https://www.theguardian.com/music/2018/apr/22/avicii-obituary |url-status=live }}</ref> He rose to prominence in 2011 with his single "[[Levels (Avicii song)|Levels]]". His debut studio album, ''[[True (Avicii album)|True]]'' (2013), blended electronic music with elements of multiple genres and received generally positive reviews. It peaked in the top 10 in more than 15 countries and topped international charts;<ref>[https://www.australian-charts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Avicii&titel=True&cat=a Avicii – True] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170611060520/https://australian-charts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Avicii&titel=True&cat=a |date=11 June 2017 }}. Australian-charts.com. Retrieved 16 October 2015.</ref><ref>[https://danishcharts.dk/showitem.asp?interpret=Avicii&titel=True&cat=a Avicii – True] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201021101315/https://danishcharts.dk/showitem.asp?interpret=Avicii&titel=True&cat=a |date=21 October 2020 }}. danishcharts.dk. Retrieved 16 October 2015.</ref><ref>[https://www.swedishcharts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Avicii&titel=True&cat=a Avicii – True] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170811183148/https://www.swedishcharts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Avicii&titel=True&cat=a |date=11 August 2017 }}. Swedishcharts.com. Retrieved 16 October 2015.</ref><ref name=":8">[https://www.billboard.com/artist/280336/Avicii/chart?f=322 Avicii – Chart history] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170626160559/https://www.billboard.com/artist/280336/avicii/chart?f=322 |date=26 June 2017 }}. ''Billboard''
